Sure enough, in a recent version of a graphics library that graphviz 
uses to generate bitmap images, support for the GIF format was removed. 
  It has now been restored, but it seems that the version of graphviz 
available for download was built with the library version without GIF 
support.  But in any case, dot supports PNG and SVG formats, which can 
be viewed in an external browser.  In the attached file, I have changed 
the default to display SVG in a web browser.  Put it in folder 
&#39;site_packages/MixMaster&#39; in the Python library folder to update 
MixMaster.

